<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, AND FENDERS - 5000i, 9000i - REMOVE - REMOVE
        HEADLIGHT AND TURN SIGNAL LENS ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>REMOVE HEADLIGHT AND TURN SIGNAL LENS ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Headlight and Turn Signal Lens Assembly on 9100
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9200
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9400
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9900
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SFA) 9900
                <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                (SFA) and 5900
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SFA)
            </title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900451">Figure 51</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mounting screws (Item 1) securing headlight bezel (Item 2) to the
                    headlight/turn signal assembly (Item 3). Remove headlight bezel from headlight/turn signal assembly,
                    save mounting screws and headlight bezel for installation if not damaged, driver side shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900451" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001a5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Remove Headlight Bezel on 9100
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9200
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9400
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                    (SFA) and 5900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA)
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT BEZEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT/TURN SIGNAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900452">Figure 52</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With headlight bezel (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900451">Figure 51</hotlnk>) removed, remove two mounting screws (Item 1), located
                    in upper and lower corners of the turn signal lens assembly (Item 2), save mounting screws for
                    installation, driver side shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900452" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001a6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Remove Turn Signal Lens Assembly Mounting Screws on 9100
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9200
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9400
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                    (SFA) and 5900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA)
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TURN SIGNAL LENS ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900453">Figure 53</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Once the two mounting screws (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900452">Figure 52</hotlnk>) are removed, rotate the turn signal lens assembly
                    (Item 1) outward, away from the hood/fender assembly (Item 2). When the turn signal lens assembly
                    reaches a certain point, it will pop out of the headlight/turn signal assembly mounting bracket
                    (Item 3), driver side shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900453" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001a7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Remove Turn Signal Lens Assembly on 9100
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9200
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9400
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                    (SFA) and 5900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA)
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL LENS ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD/FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT/TURN SIGNAL ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900454">Figure 54</hotlnk>
                    for all items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>If necessary, reach behind the headlight (Item 1) and pull the headlight/turn signal assembly
                    wiring harness (Item 2) toward the outside of the hood/fender assembly (Item 3). This will allow the
                    turn signal lens assembly (Item 4) to be pulled far enough away from the hood/fender assembly to
                    reach the turn signal bulb socket (Item 5) and remove it from the turn signal lens assembly, driver
                    side shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Once the turn signal bulb socket (Item 5) is removed, the turn signal bulb (Item 6) can
                    be removed, driver side shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat this procedure to remove the passenger side turn signal lens assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900454" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001a8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Remove Turn Signal Lens Assembly Bulb on 9100
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9200
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9400
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SBA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA), 9900
                    <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                    (SFA) and 5900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    (SFA)
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIRING HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD/FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TURN SIGNAL LENS ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. TURN SIGNAL BULB SOCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. TURN SIGNAL BULB</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HEADLIGHT/TURN SIGNAL ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
